-- South African Stocks Retreat For Second Day, Led by Anglo, BHP and SacOil
-- B y   G a r t h   T h e u n i s s e n   a n d   N i c k y   S m i t h
-- 2010-10-27T16:10:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/south-african-stocks-anglo-american-bhp-billiton-coronation.html
South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All
Share Index  retreated for a second day, falling 177.94, or 0.6
percent, to 29,955.84 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
South African market today.  Anglo American Plc (AGL SJ), the diversified mining company
that makes up about 10 percent of South Africa’s benchmark stock
index, dropped for a second day, losing 2.91 rand, or 0.9
percent, to 319 rand as copper, nickel, tin and aluminum alloy
declined.  BHP Billiton Plc  (BIL SJ), the world’s largest mining
company, slid 2.40 rand, or 1 percent, to 239.60 rand.  Anglo Platinum Ltd.  (AMS SJ), the world’s largest producer
of the precious metal, fell 11.89 rand, or 1.7 percent, to
675.01 rand. The company faces strike action in support of
workers at its Mototolo mine joint-venture with Xstrata Plc, the
National Union of Mineworkers said. Platinum prices also fell
for the first time in four days.  Mvelaphanda Group Ltd. (MVG SJ), an investment holding
company, gained 6 cents, or 1.1 percent, to 5.39 rand, the
biggest gain in a week. The company will list shares in its
Mvelaserve unit on Johannesburg’s stock exchange on Nov. 29 and
will spin off the unit to shareholders at a ratio of 25
Mvelaserve shares for every 100 shares in Mvela Group. The stock
will be distributed to shareholders on Dec. 3.  SacOil Holdings Ltd.  (SCL SJ), the Johannesburg-based crude
explorer with a concession in the Democratic Republic of Congo,
fell for a second day, dropping 3 cents, or 1.8 percent, to 1.60
rand. The company said per-share earnings will be lower in the
six months to Aug. 31 compared with the corresponding period the
previous year, according to a stock exchange statement.  To contact the reporters on this story:
